          "id": "078c22ebd58b89be918f95fa86dae8c3ab465574",
          "message": "feat: add Kimi-K2.5-MXFP4 to CI and enable dual-stream MoE for torch.compile (#375)\n\n* feat: add Kimi-K2.5-MXFP4 to CI and enable dual-stream MoE for torch.compile\n\nAdd Kimi-K2.5-MXFP4 model support:\n- CI accuracy test (tp=4, GSM8K threshold=0.93)\n- Nightly benchmark (tp=4, with HSA_NO_SCRATCH_RECLAIM=1)\n- workflow_dispatch toggle for manual runs\n\nEnable dual-stream MoE under torch.compile PIECEWISE mode:\n- Register dual_stream_moe_forward as custom op (opaque to Dynamo)\n- Remove mori dependency and PIECEWISE compilation level restriction\n- Refactor DeepseekV2MoE.forward into routed_expert_forward + combine_outputs\n- Shared experts run on alt CUDA stream, routed experts on main stream\n\nOther improvements:\n- atom_test.sh: add trust_remote_code=True to lm_eval model_args\n- Simplify model-enabled check using toJson(inputs) dynamic lookup\n\n* fix: add fusion check in single_stream_moe_forward\n\nWhen aiter fusion is enabled (e.g. DeepSeek), shared_experts module is\nnot created but n_shared_experts is still set. Add the\nis_rocm_aiter_fusion_shared_expert_enabled() check to prevent\nAttributeError which causes graph break under torch.compile.",
